The executable checks confirm the key code claims and current counts: 39 regression entries, 16 Playwright cases × 2 projects, static guards PASS, TypeScript no-emit PASS, and clean diff whitespace. I also found one material release-gate defect: `verify-foundation.ps1` invokes each disposable/RLS lane at lines 17–25 but does not check `$LASTEXITCODE` after those lanes; only the final Playwright lane is checked. A failed intermediate lane could therefore be overwritten by a later success and still print PASS. I’m finishing the scope and credential/evidence reconciliation around that finding.
